headline: Lockheed Martin Partners With Australia To Transform C-130J Aircrew Training
summary: Lockheed Martin (NYSE:LMT) has secured a contract through Wright-Patterson Air Force Base to supply the Royal Australian Air Force (RAAF) with advanced C-130J training devices and upgrades. Announced on Wednesday, this deal underscores the company’s ongoing collaboration with the RAAF and aims to enhance their training capabilities significantly. Lockheed Martin Strengthens Ties With Australia The delivery of these devices is scheduled to commence in 2029. The package includes two Weapon Systems
